Multimedia Platforms, Inc., Prior to Reverse Merger With Multimedia Platforms LLC: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 6:58 AM ET
Software

Company Overview of Multimedia Platforms, Inc., Prior to Reverse Merger With Multimedia Platforms LLC



Snapshot People




Company Overview
As of February 2, 2015, Multimedia Platforms, Inc. was acquired by Multimedia Platforms LLC, in a reverse merger transaction. Sports Media Entertainment Corp. sells computer monitoring software products for parents, corporations, and educational facilities under the ExploreAnywhere name in the United States. The company develops and sells two cloud based computer software monitoring products, including Spybuddy 2013, an Internet spy software and computer monitoring product that allows users to monitor various areas of a PC; and Keylogger Pro 2013, a software, which records keystrokes typed on a keyboard layout, as well as a range of passwords, emails, chats, and social network activity typed...
As of February 2, 2015, Multimedia Platforms, Inc. was acquired by Multimedia Platforms LLC, in a reverse merger transaction. Sports Media Entertainment Corp. sells computer monitoring software products for parents, corporations, and educational facilities under the ExploreAnywhere name in the United States. The company develops and sells two cloud based computer software monitoring products, including Spybuddy 2013, an Internet spy software and computer monitoring product that allows users to monitor various areas of a PC; and Keylogger Pro 2013, a software, which records keystrokes typed on a keyboard layout, as well as a range of passwords, emails, chats, and social network activity typed by users of a computer. It sells its software products in a digital download format through its Website, exploreanywhere.com; and a network of online affiliate Websites. The company was formerly known as Explore Anywhere Holding Corporation and changed its name to Sports Media Entertainment Corp. in December 2013. The company was incorporated in 1996 and is based in Nashua, New Hampshire.
Detailed Description


1 Tara BoulevardSuite 200Nashua, NH 03062United StatesFounded in 1996



Phone: 617-203-1794

Fax: 877-657-9457








